.TH "kexec_add_buffer" 9 "kexec_add_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kexec_add_buffer \- place a buffer in a kexec segment
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" kexec_add_buffer
.BI "(struct kexec_buf *kbuf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kbuf" 12
Buffer contents and memory parameters.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function assumes that kexec_mutex is held.
On successful return, \fIkbuf->mem\fP will have the physical address of
the buffer in memory.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative errno on error.
